1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the backhaul connectivity in cellular wireless networks and proposes an alternate model using open access femtocells. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization algorithm used to determine user association in the proposed model. This involves information theory concepts such as channel conditions and interference. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper discusses the communication and networking aspects of cellular wireless networks, specifically the backhaul connectivity. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed model involves a system of third-party providers and cellular providers, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed model involves the use of multiple small cells and third-party providers, which can be analyzed using distributed computing concepts.
